body:
_This is a proposal for sharing and composing functionalities across connectors._

## Description

The logic for our "show more" feature is kind of all over the place and is part of the connector logic itself:

- Binds `toggleShowMore` to get a single function reference
- Takes care of keeping track of the `isShowingMore` state
- Pollutes the widget scope: `isShowingMore`, `toggleShowMore`, `cachedToggleShowMore`, `createToggleShowMore`, `getLimit` ([see source](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/531bbe883ab956063db6d7af59840b92addb8fff/src/connectors/hierarchical-menu/connectHierarchicalMenu.js#L98-L116))

https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/531bbe883ab956063db6d7af59840b92addb8fff/src/connectors/hierarchical-menu/connectHierarchicalMenu.js#L98-L116

This PR introduces a new pattern for subscribing a widget to a "show more" behavior with a dedicated logic.

This refactors the usage in:

- `connectRefinementList`
- `connectMenu`
- `connectHierarchicalMenu`

## Usage

```ts
function connectHierarchicalMenu(render, unmount) {
  // Instantiate the higher-order function
  const withShowMore = createWithShowMore();

  return widgetParams => {
    // ...

    return withShowMore(
      ({ toggleShowMore, isShowingMore, onToggleShowMore }) => ({
        // ...

        render(renderProps) {
          onToggleShowMore(this.render.bind(this, renderProps));

          // ...
        },
      })
    );
  };
}
```

## Alternative names

The current working name of this category of features is `enhancers`.

Other names I have in mind:

- `wrappers`
- `hofs` (higher-order functions)

Feel free to suggest some more.

## Next steps

If you'd like to use this pattern in our codebase, it can be composed with other enhancers like `withSearchForFacetValues`:

```ts
function connectHierarchicalMenu(render, unmount) {
  // Instantiate the higher-order function
  const withShowMore = createWithShowMore();
  const withSearchForFacetValues = createWithSearchForFacetValues();

  return widgetParams => {
    // ...

    return withSearchForFacetValues(
      ({ searchForFacetValues, onSearchForFacetValues }) =>
        withShowMore(({ toggleShowMore, isShowingMore, onToggleShowMore }) => ({
          // Widget definition
        }))
    );
  };
}
```
